[2] Pennsylvania
Date: Thu 8 Nov 2018, 12:44 AM
Source: KDKA [edited]
https://pittsburgh.cbslocal.com/2018/11/08/pennsylvania-health-department-hepatisis-a-outbreak/


The Pennsylvania Department of Health is warning about a Hepatitis A outbreak in our region. So far in 2018, there have been 81 cases in Pennsylvania. That is an 80% increase over the past 5 years. Allegheny County has had 8 cases reported within the past month [October 2018].

"This year [2018] seems pretty unusual with the amount of hepatitis A that's spreading. This seems to be quite isolated, in a pocket. They do believe that this is possibly related to the IV drug abuse that's so prevalent in our area," said Dr. Brent Rau, of Allegheny General Hospital.

Pennsylvania is not the only state being affected by the outbreak. Hepatitis A cases have also been reported in Ohio, West Virginia, Michigan, Florida and North Carolina.

