[Outbreaks of hepatitis A continue in a number of states of the USA. Kentucky and West Virginia by far lead the country in cases. The mode of transmission in these outbreaks (Kentucky is reporting more than 100 new cases per week) parallels that of a 3rd world country related to poor sanitation rather than a particular contaminated food vehicle. Because of this, a change in the prevention paradigm is needed to address the needs of this underserved group of Americans. - Mod.LL

